cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.CE

This paper discusses the integration of LiFi and WiFi technologies for indoor wireless communication, which falls under the category of network infrastructure and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses modulation techniques and illumination requirements, which are related to information theory and multimedia systems, respectively, making cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also touches upon physical layer security, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR), and cell deployment, which is related to computer engineering (cs.CE).
